We study the sensitivity of Soft Resets where \(\gamma\) is defined per layer when trained on random-label MNIST (data efficient). We fix the learning rate to \(\alpha=0.1\). We study the sensitivity of learning rate for the drift parameter, \(\eta_{\gamma}\), as well as \(\nu\) - initial prior standard deviation rescaling, and \(s\) - posterior standard deviation rescaling parameter.

